PART VII: SECURITY AND RESPONSIBLE DISCLOSURE
================================================================================

21. SECURITY EXPECTATIONS

The BEVoid Project has not undergone formal security auditing. The Software
may contain vulnerabilities. Users should:

  - Conduct their own security assessments
  - Not assume the Software is secure for any purpose
  - Implement additional security measures as needed
  - Monitor for security updates and advisories

22. REPORTING VULNERABILITIES

If You discover a security vulnerability in the BEVoid Project:

  DO:
  - Report it privately to the Project maintainers
  - Provide sufficient detail to understand and reproduce the issue
  - Allow reasonable time for the maintainers to develop a fix
  - Follow up to confirm the fix addresses the issue

  DO NOT:
  - Publicly disclose the vulnerability before a fix is available
  - Exploit the vulnerability for personal gain or harm
  - Report the vulnerability in public issue trackers or forums
  - Share details with third parties without maintainer consent

23. DISCLOSURE TIMELINE

The Project aims to follow this timeline for vulnerability response:

  - Acknowledge receipt: Within 48 hours
  - Assess severity: Within 7 days
  - Develop and test fix: Within 30-90 days (depending on severity)
  - Publish fix and advisory: As soon as practicable
  - Public disclosure: After fix is available and users have had time to update

24. ACKNOWLEDGMENT

Security researchers who report vulnerabilities responsibly will be
acknowledged in the Project's security advisories (unless they prefer to
remain anonymous).

