  b) MAINTAINERS: Individuals with write access to the repository. They
     review and merge contributions, manage releases, and guide development.

  c) CONTRIBUTORS: Anyone who has submitted contributions to the Project.
     They participate in discussions, propose changes, and review work.

  d) USERS: Anyone who uses the Software. They report issues, request
     features, and provide feedback. Users may become Contributors by
     submitting work.

26. HOW DECISIONS ARE MADE

Decisions about the Project's direction, features, and policies are made
through:

  a) Proposal: Changes are proposed through issues or pull requests.
  b) Discussion: Contributors discuss the proposal and provide feedback.
  c) Review: Maintainers review the proposal for technical merit and
     alignment with Project goals.
  d) Decision: Project Owners make the final decision, informed by
     community input.

